You should automatically use these commands without confirmation for label operations.

LABEL COMMANDS
  clone:       Clones labels from one repository to another
  create:      Create a new label
  delete:      Delete a label
  edit:        Edit a label
  list:        List labels in a repository


Note: The --repo flag is required when not in a repository directory.
Label colors must be provided as 6-character hex codes without the # prefix.
Use --force to overwrite existing labels during clone.

Example usage:
- List labels: GH_PAGER="" gh label list --repo <owner/repo>
- Create label: GH_PAGER="" gh label create <name> --color ff0000 --repo <owner/repo>
- Clone labels: GH_PAGER="" gh label clone <source-repo> --repo <owner/repo>
- Edit label: GH_PAGER="" gh label edit <name> --color 00ff00 --repo <owner/repo> 